e%2C%20meaning%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipgf_062918_best-dinnerware-sets-20%26h%3D7509c32688776dd8edd51f968b93166d033218c6a2b1631e6062d9be391b6ab0%26postID%3D61b8efc6f2a36b1ac9f41c61%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fbest-dinnerware%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.lenox.com%252Fpages%252Freplacement-promise%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20company%20will%20replace%20any%20Lenox%20brand%20dinnerware%20and%20serveware%20you%20break%20for%20free%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20long%20as%20the%20replacements%20are%20available.%20(This%20is%20a%20recent%20improvement%20from%20their%20previous%20policy%20of%20replacing%20items%20at%2050%25%20off.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225d29a37c-89ba-4e74-af53-dfbd192f0c50%5C%22%3EWhat%20to%20buy%3A%3C%2Fh3%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDinnerware%20materials%3Cp%3EWhen%20shopping%20for%20dinnerware%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20consider%20a%20material%20that%20meets%20your%20durability%20and%20lifestyle%20needs.%20The%20main%20dinnerware%20materials%20you'll%20find%20are%20porcelain%2C%20fine%20and%20bone%20china%2C%20stoneware%2C%20and%20melamine.%20In%20general%2C%20porcelain%20and%20china%20are%20more%20delicate%2C%20while%20stoneware%20and%20melamine%20are%20heartier%20and%20can%20go%20in%20the%20dishwasher.%20Here's%20a%20breakdown%20of%20the%20different%20material%20types%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EChina%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20durable%2C%20lightweight%2C%20and%20often%20reserved%20for%20special%20occasions.%20There%20are%20two%20types%20of%20china%20%E2%80%94%20bone%20and%20fine.%20Bone%20china%20is%20made%20by%20combining%20china%20clay%20and%20cow%20bone%20ash%2C%20which%20forms%20a%20translucent%2C%20milky%20look%20that's%20timeless%20and%20classy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20both%20bone%20and%20fine%20china%20may%20be%20associated%20with%20special%20occasions%2C%20they're%20also%20a%20surprisingly%20good%20option%20for%20everyday%20use%20%E2%80%94%20both%20bone%20china%20and%20fine%20china%20are%20durable%20dinnerware%20options%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipgf_062918_best-dinnerware-sets-20%26h%3D522ed6baa5885018b7fb520d66684da2413272d859bed13e43e8e7cf68102984%26postID%3D61b8efc6f2a36b1ac9f41c61%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fbest-dinnerware%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.wedgwood.com%252Fen-us%252Fwelcome-to-wedgwood%252Fbuying-guides%252Fa-guide-to-bone-china%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewith%20bone%20china%20being%20the%20most%20durable%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20prefer%20the%20look%20of%20bone%20china%2C%20you%20will%20pay%20a%20higher%20price.%20When%20shopping%20for%20bone%20china%2C%20make%20sure%20you%20look%20at%20the%20percentage%20of%20cow%20bone%20ash%20content.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnoritake.com.au%2Fblog%2Fdifference-between-bone-china-and-fine-china%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Noritake%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20standard%20amount%20of%20bone%20ash%20should%20be%2030%25.%20If%20you%20don't%20see%20the%20percentage%20listed%20in%20the%20product%20details%2C%20ask%20the%20manufacturer%20before%20purchasing%3B%20brands%20can%20claim%20their%20dinnerware%20is%20bone%20china%20with%20even%20a%20small%20percentage%20of%20bone%20ash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EPorcelain%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20prefer%20a%20slightly%20heavier%2C%20sturdier%20feel%20for%20dinnerware%2C%20porcelain%20is%20a%20great%20option.%20Porcelain%20%E2%80%94%20a%20nonporous%20ceramic%20%E2%80%94%20is%20fired%20at%20a%20high%20temperature%20making%20it%20durable%2C%20and%20it's%20oven-%2C%20dishwasher-%20and%20microwave-safe.%20Porcelain%20dinnerware%20usually%20comes%20in%20white%20but%20you%20can%20find%20it%20in%20different%20colors%20and%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EStoneware%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStoneware%20is%20a%20nonporous%20ceramic%20dinnerware%20made%20from%20stoneware%20clay%20that's%20fired%20at%20a%20high%20temperature.%20It's%20thicker%20than%20both%20porcelain%20and%20china%2C%20and%20you'll%20often%20find%20this%20dinnerware%20material%20at%20your%20favorite%20restaurant%20for%20this%20reason.%20This%20type%20of%20dinnerware%20requires%20a%20little%20more%20maintenance%20as%20it%20doesn't%20handle%20extreme%20heat%20or%20extreme%20cold%20temperatures%20well.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EMelamine%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20many%20dinnerware%20materials%20are%20durable%2C%20they%20aren't%20completely%20shatterproof%20like%20melamine.%20Melamine%20is%20a%20type%20of%20plastic%20that's%20food%20safe.%20Whitmore%20suggests%20it's%20worth%20investing%20in%20a%20chic%20melamine%20set%20if%20you%20have%20small%20children%20in%20your%20household%3B%20it%20also%20doubles%20as%20dinnerware%20for%20outside%20or%20poolside%20dinner%20parties.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Ffood%2Fchemical-contaminants-food%2Fmelamine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20FDA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20isn't%20microwave%20safe.%20And%20even%20though%20melamine%20has%20come%20a%20long%20way%20in%20appearance%20%E2%80%94%20often%20looking%20like%20a%20higher-end%20material%20%E2%80%94%20it%20may%20be%20too%20casual%20for%20a%20formal%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20chose%20the%20best%20dinnerware%3Cp%3EA%20nice%20dinnerware%20set%20is%20something%20you'll%20keep%20for%20years%20to%20come%2C%20and%20perhaps%20even%20pass%20down%20generations%2C%20so%20we%20chose%20brands%20that%20have%20been%20around%20for%20decades%2C%20or%20even%20centuries.%20After%20speaking%20with%20cookbook%20author%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpizzazzerie.com%2Fbookshop%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECourtney%20Whitmore%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20wedding%20caterer%20Bruce%20Roy%20and%20doing%20our%20own%20research%2C%20we%20selected%20trusted%20brands%20that%20provide%20the%20best%20customer%20service%20and%20have%20plenty%20in%20stock%20so%20you%20can%20easily%20replace%20or%20add%20to%20items%20in%20your%20collection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDinnerware%20FAQs%3Ch3%3EHow%20many%20dinnerware%20pieces%20do%20I%20need%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20buy%20dinnerware%20as%20open%20stock%2C%20by%20the%20place%20setting%2C%20or%20in%20sets%20with%20services%20of%20two%20to%2012%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20always%20advise%20people%20to%20have%20a%20dinnerware%20set%20for%20at%20least%2010%20%5Bpeople%5D%20in%20addition%20to%20a%20selection%20of%20platters%2C%20trays%20or%20serving%20pieces%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Whitmore.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20mix%20and%20match%20pieces%20to%20coordinate%20a%20cohesive%20look%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrands%20may%20differ%20in%20what%20pieces%20they%20include%20in%20their%20place%20settings%20or%20sets.%20If%20you%20are%20shopping%20for%20a%20dinnerware%20set%20for%20a%20formal%20dinner%2C%20make%20sure%20each%20place%20setting%20%26quot%3Bincludes%20the%20key%20pieces%20like%20dinner%20plate%2C%20salad%20plate%2C%20a%20teacup%20and%20saucer%20and%20dessert%20plate%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Roy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EWhat's%20the%20best%20type%20of%20dinnerware%20to%20buy%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20you%20plan%20on%20using%20your%20dinnerware%20will%20determine%20the%20type%20you%20need.%20For%20formal%20special%20occasions%2C%20you%20probably%20want%20porcelain%20or%20china.%20Stoneware%20and%20melamine%20are%20sturdier%20and%20dishwasher-safe%2C%20more%20suited%20to%20everyday%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EWhat%20style%20of%20dinnerware%20should%20I%20buy%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20style%20of%20dinnerware%20depends%20on%20your%20personal%20aesthetic%20and%20how%20you%20plan%20on%20using%20your%20dinnerware.%20If%20it's%20for%20everyday%20use%2C%20you%20can%20play%20with%20different%20colors%20and%20patterns.%20If%20you're%20looking%20for%20dinnerware%20for%20a%20formal%20table%20setting%2C%20it's%20best%20to%20keep%20it%20simple.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20always%20recommend%20a%20classic%20white%20set%20with%20a%20little%20extra%20detail%20like%20a%20subtle%20scallop%20edge%20or%20a%20beaded%20trim%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Whitmore.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20use%20it%20all%20year%20long%20and%20switch%20out%20the%20colors%20of%20table%20linens%2C%20flowers%20and%20decor%20to%20coordinate%20color%20schemes%20with%20holidays%20and%20occasions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EWhat%20are%20the%20best%20dishes%20for%20everyday%20use%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20you%20want%20a%20material%20that's%20dishwasher-%20and%20microwave-safe.%20You%20may%20even%20want%20an%20oven-safe%20material.%20Overall%2C%20they%20should%20be%20versatile%20and%20sturdy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20stoneware%20and%20melamine%20are%20obvious%20choices%2C%20some%20china%20and%20porcelain%20are%20dishwasher-safe%20but%20are%20still%20more%20delicate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EWhat%20is%20the%20most%20chip-resistant%20dinnerware%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EPorcelain%2C%20bone%20china%2C%20stoneware%2C%20and%20melamine%20all%20resist%20chips%20and%20scratches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3EWhere%20can%20I%20purchase%20replacements%20for%20broken%20china%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20receive%20a%20broken%20or%20damaged%20dinnerware%20item%20when%20you%20first%20purchase%20it%2C%20most%20companies%20will%20replace%20the%20product%20for%20free.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20replace%20a%20broken%20item%20from%20your%20collection%2C%20check%20to%20see%20if%20the%20brand%20offers%20a%20replacement%20program.%20If%20you%20register%20your%20dinnerware%2C%20brands%20like%20Lenox%20and%20Noritake%20offer%20a%20replacement%20program%20at%20a%20discounted%20price%20or%20free%20as%20long%20as%20the%20items%20are%20still%20actively%20being%20sold.%20You%20can%20also%20check%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.replacements.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReplacements%2C%20Ltd.%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20world's%20largest%20retailer%20of%20dinnerware%20(with%20more%20than%20425%2C000%20patterns%20available)%2C%20to%20search%20for%20a%20replacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-dinnerware%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1776812062000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6531304596f7540cd060410b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-dinnerware%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Having%20high-end%20dishes%20set%20can%20make%20a%20table%20feel%20extravagant.%20These%20are%20the%2022%20best%20dinnerware%20sets%20we've%20found%20from%20across%20the%20web.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Farima%20Ferguson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-dinnerware%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20disinfect%20every%20room%20in%20your%20house%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224554%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22medical%20coro