l%253F_encoding%253DUTF8%2526amp%253Bpsc%253D1%2526amp%253BrefRID%253D1RVD91J8A67B4XR7DA82%2526amp%253BlinkCode%253Dsl1%2526amp%253Btag%253Dbiip_053119_how-to-keep-flowers-alive-20%2526amp%253BlinkId%253Dbecc060bab10caefa3e6b6b48850e7ca%2526amp%253Blanguage%253Den_US%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekitchen%20scissors%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20a%20sharp%2C%20clean%20knife%20will%20also%20do.%20Cut%20at%20an%20angle%20to%20help%20the%20stems%20take%20in%20water%20more%20easily%20since%20they%20aren't%20resting%20flat%20against%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20vase.%20Experts%20suggest%20retrimming%20your%20blooms%20every%20few%20days%20for%20a%20fresh%20and%20clean%20stem.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrune%20extra%20leaves%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt's%20important%20to%20remove%20any%20leaves%20that%20fall%20below%20the%20water%20line%20to%20prevent%20bacterial%20growth.%20Check%20your%20flowers%20daily%20to%20remove%20dead%20leaves%20and%20petals.%20This%20is%20especially%20important%20in%20mixed%20bouquets%20which%20have%20multiple%20types%20of%20flowers%20that%20may%20have%20different%20blooming%20times.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EPick%20the%20right%20vase%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThis%20may%20seem%20obvious%20to%20some%20people%2C%20but%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirecutter.com%2Freviews%2Fright-vase-for-flowers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereally%20does%20make%20a%20difference%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Just%20because%20the%20florist%20hands%20you%20a%20bunch%20of%20peonies%20on%20long%20stems%20doesn't%20mean%20they%20should%20be%20put%20in%20a%20tall%20vase.%20Bigger%2C%20heavier%20blooms%20should%20be%20cut%20short%20and%20put%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiip_053119_how-to-keep-flowers-alive-20%26h%3Dec101f0df24032ffb58ab66cd42b5a1b133b78186fea79b3af3d6e6265595dcc%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f42519%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fhow-to-keep-flowers-alive-and-fresh%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fgo.skimresources.com%252F%253Fid%253D35871X943606%2526amp%253Bxs%253D1%2526amp%253Burl%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.wayfair.com%25252Fdecor-pillows%25252Fpdp%25252Fthree-posts-mifley-table-vase-w001671424.html%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elow%20vase%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20they%20can%20support%20each%20other%20when%20they%20open%20or%20have%20room%20to%20spread%20out%2C%20while%20lighter%2C%20more%20delicate%20flowers%20can%20be%20kept%20in%20a%20taller%20vase.%20Make%20sure%20you%20are%20not%20crowding%20the%20vase%20either%3B%20when%20in%20doubt%20you%20can%20always%20make%20two%20bouquets%20out%20of%20one.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EChange%20the%20water%20every%20few%20days%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EStart%20with%20a%20clean%20vase%20and%20fill%20it%20with%20room%20temperature%20water.%20When%20you%20add%20ingredients%20like%20flower%20food%20to%20the%20water%2C%20make%20sure%20they%20are%20completely%20mixed%20and%20dissolved%20before%20you%20place%20the%20flowers.%20Change%20the%20water%2C%20clean%20the%20vase%2C%20and%20re-trim%20the%20stems%20every%20few%20days.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAvoid%20heat%2C%20direct%20sunlight%2C%20windows%2C%20and%20even%20fruit%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFlowers%20will%20last%20longer%20in%20a%20cooler%20room%20and%20if%20you%20keep%20them%20out%20of%20direct%20sunlight.%20Avoid%20placing%20them%20near%20appliances%20that%20generate%20high%20or%20low%20temperatures%20like%20the%20stove%2C%20air%20conditioner%2C%20ceiling%20fans%2C%20and%20even%20your%20computer%20or%20TV.%20Open%20windows%20will%20also%20cause%20them%20to%20dehydrate%20more%20quickly%2C%20and%20keep%20them%20away%20from%20fresh%20fruit%20which%20releases%20tiny%20amounts%20of%20gas%20that%20can%20cut%20the%20lifespan%20of%20your%20blossoms.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMake%20your%20flowers%20last%20longer%20with%20additives%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Urban%20Stems%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5cbdf16ab14bf400a548c2d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EUrban%20Stems%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFlower%20food%20packet%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20pre-mixed%20packet%20that%20comes%20with%20flowers%20from%20your%20florist%20or%20grocery%20store%20is%20universally%20agreed%20by%20experts%20to%20be%20the%20best%20overall%20method%20for%20keeping%20flowers%20alive.%20It's%20the%20perfect%20mix%20of%20the%20three%20essential%20things%20flowers%20need%3A%20carbohydrates%20(sugars)%2C%20biocides%20(cleansing%20agents)%2C%20and%20acidifiers.%20These%20ingredients%20promote%20cell%20metabolism%2C%20combat%20bacteria%2C%20and%20adjust%20the%20pH%20of%20the%20water%20to%20increase%20water%20uptake.%20Experts%20recommend%20adding%20a%20new%20packet%20to%20your%20vase%20whenever%20you%20change%20the%20water%2C%20so%20ask%20for%20several%20from%20your%20florist%20if%20you%20can.%20If%20you%20run%20out%20of%20packets%2C%20try%20this%20recipe%20for%20homemade%20flower%20food%3A%201%20teaspoon%20sugar%2C%201%20teaspoon%20bleach%2C%20and%202%20teaspoons%20lemon%20or%20lime%20juice%20mixed%20into%201%20quart%20of%20water.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EVodka%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHappy%20hour%20for%20your%20flowers%20is%20officially%20a%20real%20thing.%20By%20adding%20a%20few%20drops%20of%20vodka%20to%20your%20water%2C%20you're%20slowing%20the%20wilting%20process%20through%20the%20alcohol's%20ability%20to%20decrease%20the%20production%20of%20ethylene%2C%20the%20ripening%20gas%20that%20makes%20fruits%2C%20veggies%2C%20and%20plants%20mature.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESoda%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMaybe%20you%20didn't%20know%20your%20hydrangeas%20had%20a%20sweet%20tooth%3F%20Mix%20a%20%C2%BC%20cup%20of%20soda%20into%20the%20water%20and%20watch%20how%20your%20blooms%20stay%20perky%20with%20a%20sugary%20beverage%2C%20just%20like%20a%20kid%20with%20a%20can%20of%20Sprite.%20In%20fact%2C%20that's%20the%20type%20of%20soda%20recommended%2C%20since%20a%20dark%20drink%20like%20Coke%20or%20Pepsi%20will%20turn%20the%20water%20cloudy.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAspirin%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EKeep%20your%20daisies%20from%20drooping%20by%20crushing%20an%20aspirin%20tablet%20and%20mixing%20it%20into%20your%20water.%20The%20common%20pain-reliever%20can%20lower%20the%20pH%20level%20in%20the%20water%2C%20which%20helps%20it%20travel%20through%20the%20stem%20faster%20to%20keep%20your%20flowers%20fresher%2C%20longer.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ECoins%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20copper%20in%20coins%2C%20especially%20pennies%2C%20has%20acidic%20properties%20that%20also%20fight%20bacteria%20growing%20in%20your%20water%20and%20on%20your%20flowers.%20Just%20one%20penny%20on%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20vase%20will%20help%20your%20tulips%20open%20up%2C%20but%20some%20experts%20suggest%20adding%20crushed%20aspirin%20to%20lower%20pH%20levels%20and%20increase%20water%20flow.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EApple%20cider%20vinegar%2C%20sugar%2C%20and%20bleach%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20jury's%20still%20out%20on%20this%20one%20(sorry%2C%20Mom)%2C%20but%20the%20idea%20here%20is%20that%20you're%20mimicking%20the%20flower%20food%20with%20sugar%20for%20nutrients%20and%20vinegar%20to%20acidify%20the%20water.%20The%20most%20common%20recipe%20calls%20for%202%20tablespoons%20of%20sugar%2C%202%20tablespoons%20of%20apple%20cider%20vinegar%20and%20%C2%BD%20teaspoon%20bleach%20for%20a%20quart%20vase.%20And%20if%20this%20method%20doesn't%20work%20for%20your%20flowers%2C%20there%20are%20lots%20of%20other%20things%20you%20can%20do%20with%20a%20little%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-you-can-make-with-apple-cider-vinegar-2019-5%5C%22%3EACV%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBleach%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIf%20bleach%20fights%20bacteria%20on%20floors%20and%20countertops%2C%20it%20only%20makes%20sense%20that%20it%20will%20kill%20the%20nasties%20in%20your%20vase%20water%20too.%20This%20method%20may%20be%20the%20trickiest%20since%20too%20much%20bleach%20is%20bad%20for%20your%20blossoms.%20Experts%20suggest%20just%20a%20%C2%BC%20teaspoon%20of%20bleach%20for%201%20liter%20of%20water%20and%20adding%20a%20bit%20of%20soda%20or%20vinegar%20for%20an%20acidic%20element%20that%20will%20help%20the%20water%20flow%20through%20your%20flowers.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ERefrigerator%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThere's%20a%20reason%20why%20your%20florist%20usually%20keeps%20flowers%20in%20a%20large%20commercial%20fridge.%20This%20method%20will%20keep%20your%20buds%20fresher%20for%20longer%20%E2%80%93%20if%20you%20remember%20to%20do%20it%20every%20night.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECheck%20out%20our%20guide%20to%20the%20best%20flower%20delivery%20services%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%221800flowers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5cfa719011e20533711dbe13%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3E1-800-FLOWERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fgifts%2Fbest-flower-delivery-service%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20best%20online%20flower%20delivery%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20you%20know%20how%20to%20keep%20fresh-cut%20flowers%20alive%20as%20long%20as%20possible%2C%20you're%20ready%20to%20order%20some%20blooms.%20We've%20done%20a%20lot%20of%20testing%20to%20choose%20the%20best%20online%20flower%20delivery%20services.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-keep-flowers-alive-and-fresh%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1776811742000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5cfa728911e2051f82383c83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-keep-flowers-alive-and-fresh%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Don't%20have%20a%20green%20thumb%3F%20No%20problem.%20Here's%20how%20to%20keep%20fresh%20flowers%20alive%20and%20fresh%20longer%20after%20they're%20cut.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Lilah%20Nicolaidis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-keep-flowers-alive-and-fresh%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%2010%20best%20ways%20to%20cool%20down%20a%20room%20without%20AC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22boy%20fan%20cool%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5eebb1dcaee6a8028e69eca7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThere%20are%20many%20tricks%20to%20cool%20down%20a%20room%20without%20AC.%3Cp%3ECatherine%20Falls%20Commercial%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETo%20cool%20down%20a%20room%20without%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-portable-air-conditioner%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20make%20sure%20to%20use%20window%20fans%2C%20ceiling%20fans%2C%20or%20tower%20fans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKeep%20your%20room%20cooler%20all%20day%20by%20covering%20windows%20to%20prevent%20heat%20from%20sunlight%20coming%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EYou%20can%20also%20reduce%20humidity%2C%20block%20air%20leaks%2C%20and%20ventilate%20out%20hot%20air%20to%20cool%20your%20entire%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESummers%20are%20getting%20hotter%2C%20and%20extreme%20heat%20events%20are%20only%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fclimate-indicators%2Fclimate-change-indicators-heat-waves%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecoming%20more%20common%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20in%20places%20like%20the%20Pacific%20Northwest%2C%20where%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fusafacts.org%2Farticles%2F91-of-households-nationwide-have-air-conditioning-44-of-those-in-seattle-do%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20households%20have%20air%20conditioning%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20can%20you%20do%20when%20the%20heat%20hits%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFans%20are%20a%20powerful%20tool%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20air%20conditioning%20or%20are%20running%20it%20at%20a%20higher%20temperature.%20Fans%20are%20generally%20cheaper%20to%20buy%20and%20install%20than%20AC%20units.%20Plus%2C%20they%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC5854721%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebetter%20for%20the%20environment%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they%20use%20less%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20AC%20costs%20homeowners%20about%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Fenergysaver%2Fhome-cooling-systems%2Fair-conditioning%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAir%2520conditioners%2520use%2520about%25206%2Cinto%2520the%2520air%2520each%2520year.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2429%20billion%20each%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20United%20States%20Department%20of%20Energy%20(DOE).%20Fans%20are%20far%20more%20energy-efficient%20and%20cost-effective.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221834%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ac%20v.%20fan%20energy%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5eebae232618b9335b76ad75%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFans%20can%20be%20an%20energy-efficient%20alternative%20to%20AC.%3Cp%3ERuobing%20Su%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20some%20fans%20on%20deck%2C%20you%20can%20optimize%20how%20you%20use%20them%20for%20the%20best%2C%20coolest%20results.%20There%20are%20also%20plenty%20of%20other%20steps%20you%20can%20take%20to%20keep%20your%20home%20cool.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%2010%20ways%20to%20cool%20down%20a%20room%20using%20fans%20and%20other%20items%20you%20can%20easily%20buy%20or%20might%20already%20have%20in%20your%20home%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22767bd6cc-dc94-4847-9dfd-0e8c3af84518%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Put%20window%20fans%20to%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22window%20fan%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5eebb19d2618b93534136144%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWindow%20fans%20should%20only%20be%20used%20in%20certain%20cases.%3Cp%3ERicky%20Kresslein%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWindow%20fans%20are%20installed%20in%20open%20windows%20to%20draw%20cold%20air%20in%20and%20push%20hot%20air%20out%2C%20and%20can%20be%20set%20up%20to%20cool%20an%20entire%20house.%20Here's%20how%20to%20use%20window%20fans%20most%20effectively.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOnly%20turn%20window%20fans%20on%20when%20it's%20cooler%20outside%20than%20inside.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20order%20for%20window%20fans%20to%20cool%20your%20home%2C%20the%20outdoor%20temperature%20must%20be%20lower%20than%20the%20indoor%20temperature.%20That's%20going%20to%20be%20at%20nighttime%20or%20early%20in%20the%20morning.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWindow%20fans%20are%20installed%20with%20a%20fitted%20sheet%20metal%20mounting%20that%20slots%20into%20an%20open%20window%20and%20seals%20around%20the%20edges.%20So%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20opening%20or%20closing%20that%20window.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20other%20windows%20in%20your%20house%20should%20remain%20closed%20during%20the%20hottest%20part%20of%20the%20day%20and%20%E2%80%94%20when%20safe%20%E2%80%94%20open%20at%20night%20and%20early%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImportant%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Don't%20run%20a%20window%20fan%20during%20the%20hottest%20part%20of%20the%20day%20because%20it%20will%20draw%20in%20the%20hot%20afternoon%20air%2C%20making%20your%20home%20warmer%2C%20not%20cooler.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUse%20more%20than%20one%20fan%20to%20create%20a%20crosswind.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWindow%20fans%20work%20best%20when%20you%20use%20more%20than%20one%20to%20create%20a%20crosswind%2C%20which%20pushes%20the%20hot%20air%20out%20and%20draws%20the%20cool%20air%20in.%20To%20do%20this%2C%20setting%20the%20fans%20up%20in%20the%20right%20location%20is%20crucial.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20to%20be%20strategic%20about%20your%20window%20fans'%20placement%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFans%20blowing%20air%20into%20your%20house%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20%26quot%3BYou%20want%20the%20cooler%20air%20to%20blow%20inwards%2C%20so%20place%20one%20fan%20or%20more%20on%20the%20coolest%20side%20of%20your%20home%20that%20sees%20lots%20of%20shade%20%E2%80%94%20this%20will%20ideally%20be%20on%20the%20north%20side%20which%20gets%20the%20most%20shade%20%E2%80%94%20facing%20in%20towards%20the%20house%20and%20away%20from%20the%20windows%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kipnisarch.com%2Fnathan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENathan%20Kipnis%2C%20FAIA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20founder%20of%20Kipnis%20Architecture%20and%20Planning%20and%20specialist%20in%20the%20sustainability%20and%20energy%20efficiency%20of%20architectural%20design.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFans%20pushing%20air%20out%20of%20your%20house.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThen%20place%20an%20equal%20number%20of%20fans%20on%20the%20opposite%20side%20of%20your%20home%20facing%20out%20of%20your%20windows%20to%20push%20the%20hot%20air%20out.%20%26quot%3BPushing%20air%20out%20on%20the%20south%20side%20is%20ideal%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kipnis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EKeep%20as%20many%20inside%20doors%20open%20as%20possible%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20This%20will%20help%20maximize%20airflow%20throughout%20the%20house.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Ideally%2C%20you%20should%20have%20an%20equal%20number%20of%20fans%20pulling%20cool%20air%20in%20as%20pushing%20hot%20air%20out.%20However%2C%20if%20you%20have%20an%20odd%20number%20of%20fans%2C%20then%20it's%20generally%20better%20to%20have%20more%20fans%20pulling%20cool%20air%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWork%20with%20the%20design%20of%20your%20home.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20If%20you%20live%20in%20a%20multi-story%20home%2C%20place%20the%20inward-blowing%20fans%20on%20the%20lower%20floors%20where%20it's%20cooler%20and%20the%20outward-blowing%20fans%20on%20the%20upper%20floors.%20This%20method%20will%20rid%20your%20home%20of%20the%20warm%20air%20rising%20to%20the%20upper%20stories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBringing%20air%20in%20low%20on%20the%20north%20side%20and%20pushing%20it%20out%20high%20on%20the%20south%20side%20is%20ideal%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kipnis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247b6f434-1d3a-45e0-ab13-1ad666f9df4c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Optimize%20your%20ceiling%20fans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ceiling%20fan%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5eebb1745af6cc77730b8664%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECeiling%20fans%20should%20be%20rotating%20clockwise%20in%20the%20summer.%3Cp%3EWe%20Are%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECeiling%20fans%20circulate%20air%20in%20the%20room%20by%20pushing%20it%20down.%20However%2C%20they%20can%20not%20lower%20the%20temperature%20like%20a%20window%20fan%20or%20AC%20unit.%20But%20they%20can%20still%20cool%20you%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20their%20breeze%20creates%20a%20slight%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.howstuffworks.com%2Fquestion22.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewind%20chill%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20can%20help%20sweat%20evaporate%20from%20your%20skin%2C%20which%20cools%20you%20down.%20So%2C%20it's%20not%20your%20home%20that%20it's%20cooling%2C%20but%20rather%20your%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20to%20use%20your%20ceiling%20fans%20most%20effectively%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMake%20sure%20your%20ceiling%20fan%20is%20rotating%20counterclockwise.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20the%20summer%2C%20make%20sure%20your%20fan%20is%20rotating%20counterclockwise.%20This%20will%20push%20the%20air%20straight%20down%20and%20create%20that%20wind%20chill%20effect.%20Follow%20the%20instructions%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.delmarfans.com%2Feducate%2Fbasics%2Fhow-to-reverse-a-ceiling-fan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20DelMar%20Fans%20guide%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20safely%20check%20and%20change%20the%20direction%20of%20your%20ceiling%20fan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETurn%20your%20ceiling%20fan%20off%20when%20you%20leave%20the%20room.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Make%20sure%20you%20turn%20ceiling%20fans%20off%20when%20leaving%20the%20room%20because%20they%20cool%20people%2C%20not%20rooms.%20It's%20a%20waste%20of%20energy%20to%20have%20them%20switched%20on%20if%20there%20is%20no%20one%20there%20to%20feel%20the%20wind%20chill%20effect.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECombine%20a%20ceiling%20fan%20with%20your%20AC%20unit.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIf%20you%20have%20a%20ceiling%20fan%20in%20the%20same%20room%20as%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-air-conditioner%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAC%20unit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20helps%20blow%20colder%2C%20air-conditioned%20air%20throughout%20the%20room.%20This%20can%20cut%20your%20energy%20consumption%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.constellation.com%2F2018%2F05%2F10%2Fenergy-efficient-fans%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereduce%20how%20hard%20your%20air-conditioner%20has%20to%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20set%20your%20AC%20unit%20four%20degrees%20higher%2C%20combine%20it%20with%20a%20ceiling%20fan%2C%20and%20feel%20just%20as%20cool%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kipnis.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20key%20thing%20with%20AC%20is%20that%20it%20dehumidifies%20the%20air%20which%20is%20what%20helps%20make%20the%20fan%20even%20more%20effective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worth%20noting%20that%20all%20ceiling%20fans%20work%20more%20effectively%20in%20dry%20air%2C%20%26quot%3BBecause%20the%20sweat%20on%20your%20skin%20evaporates%20more%20quickly%20than%20if%20the%20air%20was%20humid%2C%20so%20you%20feel%20cooler%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kipnis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2207a5b275-f436-4231-b69d-a87afd4f7da8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Create%20an%20icy%20breeze%20with%20tower%20fans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETower%20fans%20are%20narrow%2C%20tall%2C%20and%20portable%2C%20meaning%20they%20easily%20fit%20into%20the%20corner%20of%20most%20rooms.%20They%20create%20airflow%20by%20oscillating%20from%20left%20to%20right.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20they%20work%20by%20creating%20a%20wind-chill%20effect%20rather%20than%20lowering%20the%20temperature%20of%20the%20room.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUse%20ice%20for%20extra%20cooling.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIf%20you're%20really%20struggling%20to%20stay%20cool%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20during%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20day%20when%20it's%20hottest%20outside%2C%20place%20a%20bucket%20of%20ice%20or%20a%20large%2C%20frozen%20water%20bottle%20covered%20with%20a%20damp%20cloth%20in%20front%20of%20your%20tower%20fan%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.housebeautiful.com%2Fuk%2Flifestyle%2Fa22650251%2Ffan-tricks-cool-room-heatwave-hot-weather%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomemade%20AC%20unit%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20ice%20cools%20the%20air%20pushed%20out%20by%20the%20fan%2C%20which%20then%20circulates%20around%20the%20room.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2215878771-47c7-4f24-99a9-62dd92494d32%5C%22%3EBest%20tower%20fan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20best%20tower%20fan%20Genesis%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6287ddc4b0a8be00185fd1b0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EOwen%20Burke%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGet%20the%20cold%20air%20moving%20with%20selections%20from%20our%20guide%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-electric-fan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20fans%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Our%20favorite%20tower%20fan%20has%20the%20lowest%20noise%20levels%20and%20the%20best%20energy%20efficiency%20of%20any%20large%20fan%20we%20tested%3A%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBest%20tower%20fan%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EGenesis%20Powerful%2043-Inch%20Tower%20Fan%20-%20See%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-55230-20%26h%3D956060b67b792e411456c1123d76d0937c4250c247fed0c8deff4a88ac2e35cd%26postID%3D6