ay%20heat.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EGo%20green.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fheatislands%2Fusing-trees-and-vegetation-reduce-heat-islands%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPlant%20trees%3C%2Fa%3E%20outside%20your%20home%20to%20provide%20shade%20and%20induce%20natural%20cooling%20via%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftrees-energy-conservation.extension.org%2Fhow-do-trees-cool-the-air%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevapotranspiration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20when%20moisture%20from%20a%20tree%20evaporates%20and%20cools%20the%20surrounding%20air.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EPaint%20your%20home's%20exterior%20a%20light%20color.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20dark%20exteriors%20draw%20in%20heat%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-exterior-paint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elight-colored%20exteriors%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20help%20reflect%20it%20away.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EStart%20a%20rooftop%20garden.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Also%20called%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fheatislands%2Fusing-green-roofs-reduce-heat-islands%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egreen%20roof%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20rooftop%20garden%20can%20be%20around%2030%C2%B0F%20to%2040%C2%B0F%20cooler%20than%20a%20regular%20roof.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c35170a7-0537-4ee0-9fe1-ca51952bc89a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EInsider's%20takeaway%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECooling%20down%20a%20room%20in%20the%20peak%20of%20summer%20or%20during%20a%20heat%20wave%20might%20seem%20like%20a%20difficult%20task%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFans%20can%20be%20an%20energy-efficient%20and%20cost-effective%20way%20to%20beat%20the%20heat%20during%20the%20summertime.%20You%20can%20use%20window%2C%20ceiling%2C%20or%20tower%20fans%20to