Pot's%20inception%20in%201971%2C%20its%20slow%20cookers%20have%20had%20the%20same%20basic%20parts%20of%20a%20base%2C%20an%20inner%20pot%2C%20and%20a%20lid.%20The%20base%20plugs%20into%20an%20outlet%20and%20heats%20the%20inner%20pot%2C%20which%20is%20usually%20made%20of%20stoneware.%20The%20pot%20and%20its%20contents%20are%20heated%20to%20a%20consistent%20temperature%2C%20typically%20between%20200%20and%20300%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20and%20you%20set%20it%20to%20cook%20your%20dishes%20for%20at%20least%20four%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20you%20can%20get%20excellent%20slow%20cookers%20for%20under%20%2450%2C%20including%20ones%20from%20Crock-Pot%2C%20you%20can%20also%20find%20them%20for%20less%20at%20secondhand%20stores%20if%20you're%20on%20a%20budget.%20Though%20if%20you%20go%20this%20route%2C%20be%20careful%20about%20the%20wiring%20and%20try%20to%20test%20it%20in-store%20to%20make%20sure%20it%20heats%20up%20properly%20before%20you%20make%20your%20purchase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20own%20a%20Dutch%20oven%20or%20other%20large%20oven-safe%20pot%20with%20a%20lid%2C%20you%20can%20turn%20your%20oven%20into%20a%20slow%20cooker.%20To%20convert%20any%20slow%20cooker%20recipe%2C%20just%20set%20your%20oven%20to%20200%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20for%20low%20heat%20or%20300%20degrees%20for%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2231ed5d99-77a3-435f-94d4-e6ef63e1e305%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20a%20slow%20cooker%20work%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20slow%20cooker%20gets%20its%20name%20from%20the%20time%20it%20needs%20to%20cook%20meals%20at%20low%20temperatures.%20This%20is%20different%20from%20a%20pressure%20cooker%2C%20like%20an%20Instant%20Pot%2C%20which%20uses%20intense%20pressure%20and%20a%20short%20amount%20of%20time.%20If%20you're%20interested%20in%20learning%20to%20use%20an%20Instant%20Pot%2C%20we've%20got%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fhow-to-use-an-instant-pot%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20breakdown%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20times%20vary%2C%20most%20slow%20cooker%20recipes%20call%20for%20cooking%20on%20low%20for%20eight%20hours.%20However%2C%20you%20won't%20be%20actively%20working%20on%20the%20meal%20during%20that%20time.%20The%20amount%20of%20time%20you%20spend%20preparing%20your%20meal%20for%20the%20cook%20is%20much%20shorter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c4617048-8c35-42f5-84b1-9110dbc353f5%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20use%20a%20slow%20cooker%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20most%20basic%20steps%20to%20use%20a%20slow%20cooker%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3EPrep%20your%20ingredients.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAdd%20your%20ingredients%20to%20the%20pot.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPut%20the%20lid%20in%20place.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESelect%20your%20preferred%20heating%20level.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESet%20a%20timer%20(if%20necessary)%20and%20go%20about%20your%20day.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOnce%20the%20time%20is%20up%2C%20carefully%20open%20the%20lid%20and%20enjoy%20your%20meal.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3ERecipes%20and%20ingredient%20preparation%20can%20be%20as%20involved%20as%20you%20want.%C2%A0For%20recipe%20inspiration%2C%20there%20are%20countless%20slow%20cooker%20cookbooks.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipf_051520_how-to-slow-cook-20%26h%3D08c862ad62e57c2895b22ba0a0397696184f1dd9ed23cd5afd2b141d35a4e96f%26postID%3D61b8efc8f2a36b1ac9f42dd1%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fkitchen%252Fhow-to-use-slow-cooker%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fgp%252Fproduct%252F156148640X%252Fref%253Das_li_tl%253Fie%253DUTF8%2526amp%253Btag%253Dbiipf_051520_how-to-slow-cook-20%2526amp%253Bcamp%253D1789%2526amp%253Bcreative%253D9325%2526amp%253BlinkCode%253Das2%2526amp%253BcreativeASIN%253D156148640X%2526amp%253BlinkId%253De8065b0f1175afafc88f417470eee764%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%