https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipf_051520_how-to-slow-cook-20%26h%3De78323a549311de24b27a7f47052de9aff6cddeb97371652107bca571537ccd5%26postID%3D61b8efc8f2a36b1ac9f42dd1%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fkitchen%252Fhow-to-use-slow-cooker%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fgp%252Fproduct%252FB00004OCK1%252Fref%253Das_li_tl%253Fie%253DUTF8%2526amp%253Btag%253Dbiipf_051520_how-to-slow-cook-20%2526amp%253Bcamp%253D1789%2526amp%253Bcreative%253D9325%2526amp%253BlinkCode%253Das2%2526amp%253BcreativeASIN%253DB00004OCK1%2526amp%253BlinkId%253Dc28e4899d6778134a7702575f63b12ac%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOXO%20Good%20Grips%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20smart%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20ingredients%20are%20in%20the%20pot%20and%20the%20lid%20is%20in%20place%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20choose%20a%20temperature%20setting%20and%20start%20cooking.%20Most%20slow%20cookers%20have%20just%20two%20settings%3A%20Low%20and%20High.%20Low%20heat%20is%20almost%20always%20preferable%20%E2%80%94%20after%20all%2C%20it's%20what%20gives%20%26quot%3Bslow%20cooking%26quot%3B%20its%20name%20%E2%80%94%20because%20longer%20simmers%20can%20extract%20all%20of%20the%20flavors.%20Count%20on%20meals%20cooked%20on%20the%20Low%20setting%20to%20take%20roughly%20four%20hours%20longer%20than%20those%20on%20High.%20For%20instance%2C%20dishes%20that%20take%20four%20hours%20on%20High%20will%20take%20about%20eight%20hours%20on%20Low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20Crock-Pot%20is%20cooking%2C%20let%20it%20be.%20It's%20designed%20to%20just%20work%20on%20its%20own%2C%20and%20as%20mentioned%20above%2C%20removing%20the%20lid%20frequently%20can%20mess%20with%20your%20cooking%20times%20so%20only%20do%20this%20if%20a%20recipe%20calls%20for%20it.%20Otherwise%2C%20set%20a%20timer%20(if%20your%20model%20doesn't%20have%20one%20built-in)%2C%20and%20go%20about%20your%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20come%20back%20after%20an%20hour%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20unit%20is%20hot.%20There%20are%20countless%20stories%20of%20people%20who%20have%20turned%20on%20their%20non-digital%20slow%20cooker%20only%20to%20find%20out%20hours%20later%20that%20they'd%20never%20plugged%20it%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20time%20is%20up%2C%20check%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20food%20is%20thoroughly%20cooked.%20This%20is%20unlikely%20going%20to%20be%20a%20problem%20but%20it%20doesn't%20hurt%20to%20be%20safe.%20You%20can%20use%20a%20thermometer%20in%20the%20thickest%20part%20of%20the%20meat%20and%20refer%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fsis.usda.gov%2Fwps%2Fportal%2Ffsis%2Ftopics%2Ffood-safety-education%2Fget-answers%2Ffood-safety-fact-sheets%2Fsafe-food-handling%2Fsafe-minimum-internal-temperature-chart%2Fct_index%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSDA's%20recommended%20internal%20temperatures%20guide%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Or%20just%20cut%20the%20biggest%20piece%20of%20meat%20in%20half%20and%20eyeball%20it.%20If%20it%20appears%20to%20be%20cooked%20all%20the%20way%20through%2C%20you're%20good%20to%20go.%20You%20can%20serve%20the%20meal%20in%20the%20pot%20itself%20or%20on%20a%20serving%20platter%20if%20anything%20needs%20to%20be%20sliced%20or%20cut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22089f3ba6-f12f-400a-8620-784e6fefa75f%5C%22%3EHow%20much%20liquid%20do%20I%20need%20in%20a%20slow%20cooker%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20depends%20on%20the%20recipe%20but%20when%20adding%20ingredients%2C%20remember%20that%20heat%20makes%20items%20expand.%20Therefore%2C%20if%20you%20fill%20the%20stoneware%20all%20the%20way%20up%20to%20the%20top%2C%20you're%20likely%20to%20have%20some%20of%20the%20liquids%20spill%20over%20during%20the%20cooking%20process.%20Go%20with%20the%20recipe%20and%20don't%20fill%20the%20pot%20more%20than%20two-thirds%20or%20three-quarters%20of%20the%20way%20full.%20With%20this%20in%20mind%2C%20if%20you%20plan%20on%20making%20big%20pots%20of%20food%2C%20consider%20buying%20a%20larger%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipf_051520_how-to-slow-cook-20%26h%3De0158142d0a5a2d06d038095d62f0e8cc5d2802cc57f00458b1131943451ed32%26postID%3D61b8efc8f2a36b1ac9f42dd1%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fkitchen%252Fhow-to-use-slow-cooker%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fgo.redirectingat.com%252F%253Fid%253D35871X943606%2526amp%253Burl%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.homedepot.com%25252Fp%25252FCrock-Pot-Cook-and-Carry-6-Qt-Programmable-Stainless-Steel-Slow-Cooker-SCCPVC605-S%25252F204499311%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECrock-Pot%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20should%20keep%20the%20lid%20on%20slow%20cooker%20at%20all%20times%20unless%20you%20absolutely%20need%20to%20remove%20it.%20This%20protects%20against%20temperature%20fluctuations%20since%20a%20lot%20of%20heat%20is%20released%20when%20the%20lid%20comes%20off.%20With%20the%20lid%20in%20place%2C%20moisture%20also%20stays%20contained%20so%20you%20need%20less%20liquid%20in%20the%20pot%20than%20if%20you%20were%20simmering%20on%20the%20stove%20or%20in%20the%20oven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22947ebffd-2fda-405b-9d32-23c9fc03227b%5C%22%3EWhat%20do%20you%20need%20to%20use%20a%20slow%20cooker%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20main%20benefits%20of%20slow%20cookers%20is%20that%20you%20don't%20need%20extra%20accessories%20to%20make%20a%20delicious%20meal%20%E2%80%94%20just%20the%20slow%20cooker%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipf_051520_how-to-slow-cook-20%26h%3De0158142d0a5a2d06d038095d62f0e8cc5d2802cc57f00458b1131943451ed32%26postID%3D61b8efc8f2a36b1ac9f42dd1%26postSl