0holiday%20cheer%20of%20choice%20from%20the%20bar.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESince%20some%20ingredients%20may%20cook%20at%20different%20speeds%2C%20you%20might%20want%20to%20stagger%20the%20ingredients%20you%20add.%20For%20instance%2C%20I%20like%20to%20wait%20until%20the%20final%20three%20hours%20of%20a%20low-temp%20cook%20to%20add%20potatoes%20and%20carrots%20to%20a%20roast.%20Dairy%20products%20are%20best%20added%20at%20the%20end.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20juices%20left%20in%20the%20pot%20are%20like%20liquid%20gold.%20Consider%20serving%20them%20as%20a%20sauce%20or%20gravy.%20Use%20a%20slurry%20to%20thicken%20it%20up.%20A%20slurry%20consists%20of%201%20part%20cornstarch%20to%202%20parts%20cold%20water.%20Start%20with%20small%20amounts%20(think%20a%20tablespoon%20or%20two)%20and%20slowly%20whisk%20more%20in%20until%20it%20thickens.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20slow%20cooker%20and%20Instant%20Pot%20recipes%20are%20interchangeable.%20If%20a%20meal%20takes%20an%20hour%20in%20the%20Instant%20Pot%20on%20high%20pressure%2C%20count%20on%20it%20taking%208%20hours%20in%20the%20slow%20cooker%20on%20Low.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20the%20idea%20of%20getting%20up%20early%20to%20prep%20your%20ingredients%20before%20heading%20to%20work%20sounds%20unappealing%2C%20you%20can%20prep%20items%20the%20night%20before%20and%20store%20them%20in%20the%20pot%20in%20the%20refrigerator.%20That%20way%2C%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20you%20can%20just%20take%20it%20out%2C%20put%20it%20in%20the%20base%2C%20and%20start%20cooking.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d554ce79-57d7-453d-8085-da781b5befb5%5C%22%3EEasy%20slow%20cooker%20recipes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tender%20Pot%20Roast%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ebeb7d6f0f41967db7b9284%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECafe%20Delights%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20you%20have%20a%20good%20idea%20